The paper proposes a deep learning model for ad click predictions, which falls under the category of machine learning and information retrieval. The model involves feature engineering and feature interactions, which are common topics in the subfield of deep learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of the model for click-through rate (CTR) prediction, which is a common task in information retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of the model for dense classification, which is a common task in natural language processing (cs.CL) and computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper involves the use of a novel cross network, which is a type of neural network architecture and falls under the subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
